 of a single theatrical performance, but is also informative and entertaining. Suited for informal dramatic readings as well as regular theatrical performances, Socrates on Trial will undoubtedly appeal to instructors and students, and its informative introduction enhances its value as a resource.Complete with production and classroom notes, this modern recasting of the Socrates story will make riveting reading both inside and outside the classroom.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aPhilosophersvDrama. 0aTrials (Blasphemy)zGreecezAthensvDrama. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268554340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442685543423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442685543.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK